metadata.name: EVANGELINE
metadata.description:
In 2013, I opened a box that was in my basement for over a decade.  The woman who gave it to me found it in the attic of her New Jersey childhood home in 1972.  

This discovery channeled me into a decade of ghostly experiences.  Finding breadcrumbs, tracing the Ancestors of the Attic, and Emily, led me into a "Looking Glass World," of Powerful Men, Silenced Women, Banned Books, Ciphers, and Emily Dickinson's "DIVINE IMMORTALITY"

"We've only just Begun to Uncover the Ties that Bind Us"  

"KATE'S KEEPSAKES" is a Collection of Books, Handwritten-Dated Poems, Notations, Artwork, Historical Artifacts, and over a decade of research, into the "Kate's" in Emily Dickinson's Life, Loves, and "Infinite Possibilities."  

TRUTH UNWINDS ITSELF:  LEARN MORE... https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kate_Scott_Turner
